Google’s Senior Vice President of Research, Labs, Technology & Society James Manyika sits down with Nobel laureate in Economics, Michael Spence and President of Queens' College at Cambridge, Mohamed El-Erian, for a discussion about the economic implications of artificial intelligence. #Technology #AI 

00:18 - AI's Potential for the Economy
01:56 - AI's Impact on Work and Skills
03:21 - Lessons from Past Disruptions
04:24 - Macroeconomic Optimism for Growth and Debt
